      "content": "# `perspectiveCamera`\n\nCreates a pure camera object with `viewProjection` and `position`. FOV is in degrees for the public scene API.\n\n```ts\nimport { perspectiveCamera } from \"vgpu/scene\";\n\nconst screenSize = [128, 72] as const;\nconst cam = perspectiveCamera({\n  fov: 60,\n  aspect: screenSize[0] / screenSize[1],\n  position: [0, 2, 4],\n  target: [0, 0, 0],\n});\n\ncam.position satisfies Float32Array;\n```\n",
      "summary": "Creates a pure camera object with `viewProjection` and `position`. FOV is in degrees for the public scene API.",
      "snippet": "import { perspectiveCamera } from \"vgpu/scene\";\n\nconst screenSize = [128, 72] as const;\nconst cam = perspectiveCamera({\n  fov: 60,\n  aspect: screenSize[0] / screenSize[1],\n  position: [0, 2, 4],\n  target: [0, 0, 0],\n});\n\ncam.position satisfies Float32Array;",
